node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

Today, two coasts, two distinct IPA traditions, and two JCs collide!

Brewed using the exact same recipe, save for one key differentiator in the yeast strain selected for fermentation, we're proud to offer two new collaboration beers with our friends at @alvaradostreetbrewery and @yakimachief.

Cans of My Name is JC (West Coast IPA) and My Name is Also JC (New England IPA), are now available to order!

node.text:
The second half of our HBC 586 double feature with @alvaradostreetbrewery and @yakimachief is a hazy counterpart to the West Coast IPA.

Featuring the exact same recipe, but fermented with a more familiar Trillium yeast strain, My Name is Also JC is a New England IPA with a fluffy mouthfeel and vibrant notes of orange sherbet, overripe pineapple, and creamy citrus.

This project has been a blast to work on, showcasing not only a new hop that we think will become a household name soon enough, but also shining a light on yeast's major role in the brewing process.

Snag some cans and compare for yourself! They'll become available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both PIck Up and UPS Direct. $17.20/4-pack, limit one case per person.

California folks: we've heard a rumor that the Alvarado crew might be up to something in Monterey as well...

node.text:
Y'all ready to get experimental?! Tomorrow, we're unveiling a two-part, bicoastal exploration into HBC 586, a new hop variety that is garnering quite a bit of attention amongst the hoppy brewing community...for good reason.

We teamed up with @alvaradostreetbrewery, who just so happens to be founded by another JC (hence the beer name), to brew two beers with identical recipes aside from one key ingredient: yeast.

These beers are part of a three-way collaboration with @yakimachief, who will be sampling the offerings at the upcoming Craft Brewers Conference in Denver.

My Name is JC is up first! We took insights from Alvarado's West Coast IPA techniques and utilized a clean American ale yeast to deliver a modern take on a classic. The resulting beer offers tropical aromatics, with a traditional piney bitterness and overall bright approach.

Order cans online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Curbside Pick Up and UPS Direct. $17.20/4-pack, limit one case per person. More info regarding the second half of the release coming this evening.

Featuring a sauce made from Lemon Boy Yellow Tomatoes and topped with Goldfinch Squash, both sourced from the Trillium Farm, our Summer Squash PIzza is a delicious view into our farm-to-table culinary approach.

The wood-fired pie is topped with fresh, aromatic Gremolata and Taleggio, a semi-soft, smear-ripened, and very creamy cheese from Italy's Alpine Valley.

This Friday, you could enjoy a Seaport sunrise...

(to be cont.)

'Tis the season for our annual PSA, in the form of a Double IPA, to warn against the Boston phenomenon of lodging a box truck under a low clearance overpass on Storrow Drive.

While it's a sporadic episode that can snarl traffic for hours, most of these incidents occur during college move-in weekend, typically around Labor Day. Be sure to heed the low clearance warnings at the Storrow Drive entry points!

The 2021 Storrowed recipe has been tweaked slightly, replacing Vic Secret with a hop we're quite fond of lately in Strata. We couldn't be more pleased with the results, which display mouthwatering aromas of orange-mango juice, pineapple gummies, and bright peach.

Cans will be available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pick Up and UPS Direct.
